ization, shows how causal patterns are used to develop scientific explanations, and describes how the necessarily imperfect connection between science and truth leads to researchers’ values influencing their findings. The resulting book is a tour de force, a synthesis of the study of idealization that also offers countless new insights and avenues for future exploration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aIdealism. 0aSciencexPhilosophy. 0aScience. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  acausation.  aexplanation.  aidealization.  alevels of organization.  apluralism.  ascientific aims.  aunderstanding.  avalues in science.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831107119360 cprintz978022650705740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226507194423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226507194/original  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles